# 문제 (사용자 요청)
@user_directive 2026-04-27 "kick 추상화/상상 부분에 노이즈 넣기 — 구현 코드 별도 모듈화, 재사용 용도"
@goal noise envelope generator를 단일 모듈로 추출 → kick_dispatch 외 다른 toolchain이 동일 envelope을 재사용 가능하게.

# 설계 결정
@decision_modular_extraction tool/noise_envelope.hexa as a standalone tool (CLI surface) + library entry points (noise_alpha, noise_beta, noise_byte_from_beta, noise_gamma). No shared `use` import this cycle (Sub-N hexa-lang `use` divergence) — CLI is the portable surface; kick_dispatch retains an inline copy for hot-path single-process latency (avoid an unlock-cycle per kick). Header documents the byte-equivalence contract + raw 85 audit on divergence.
@cli_surface `hexa run tool/noise_envelope.hexa <alpha|beta|gamma|--selftest>` with `--absorbed-dir`, `--bridges-dir`, `--beta-byte` flags. Mirrors hexa runtime convention (fn main() -> void + args() + skip-`run` indexing).
@sentinel_format raw 80 — `__NOISE_ENVELOPE__ <PASS|FAIL> mechanism=<a|b|g>` and `__NOISE_ENVELOPE_SELFTEST__ <PASS|FAIL>`.
@error_format raw 66 ai-native trailer on usage-fail / missing-flag / unknown-mechanism.

# 구현
@module_path tool/noise_envelope.hexa (407 lines, chflags uchg locked)
@selftest 6/6 cases PASS — α empty + α populated + β default(urandom) + β byte extractor + γ empty + γ populated. Fixture dirs isolated under /tmp/noise_envelope_selftest_*.
@cli_smoke `hexa run tool/noise_envelope.hexa alpha --absorbed-dir /tmp/none` → absorbed:none envelope; `hexa run tool/noise_envelope.hexa beta` → urandom envelope; `hexa run tool/noise_envelope.hexa gamma --bridges-dir /tmp/none --beta-byte 42` → bridge:none envelope. All three return raw 80 PASS sentinel.

# 발견 + 시정 — kick_dispatch.hexa divergence
@divergence_1 _short_hash: kick_dispatch line 204 used `shasum -a 256` (BSD-only). noise_envelope used portable cascade `(sha256sum 2>/dev/null || shasum -a 256)` per commit 59bfc967. Linux containers (debian hexa-runner) lack BSD shasum → would silently emit empty byte_hash on container fallback path.
@divergence_2 _gamma_envelope idx: kick_dispatch line 317 was `let idx = beta_byte % n` — Hexa `%` of negative numerator can yield negative result, indexing files[idx] would crash. noise_envelope explicitly handles `if idx < 0 { idx = -idx }`.
@reconciliation Mirrored both fixes back to kick_dispatch.hexa (unlock-edit-relock, raw 85 row appended) so the byte-equivalence parity contract in the noise_envelope header is honored. No semantic change to envelope output shape.
@verification `hexa run tool/kick_dispatch.hexa --help` PASS post-relock; both files now uchg locked with identical _short_hash + _gamma idx logic.

# 검증
@selftest_pass tool/noise_envelope.hexa --selftest → __NOISE_ENVELOPE_SELFTEST__ PASS (6/6)
@cli_pass alpha + beta + gamma all emit valid envelope JSON + raw 80 PASS sentinel
@kick_dispatch_pass `hexa run tool/kick_dispatch.hexa --help` (parses + dispatches usage banner)
@chflags_lock both files uchg locked; .raw-audit row 2건 추가 (unlock-edit-relock for kick_dispatch + lock for noise_envelope)

